          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":15,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. Let your body absorb the week ahead. Hydrate well and get good sleep.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run of ~5 km at 7:00–8:00 /km. This should feel conversational — you could hold a full sentence without gasping. No heroics today.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or light walking. Your aerobic system is building quietly even on off days.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run of ~5 km at 7:00–8:00 /km. Same effort as Monday — relaxed, steady, comfortable. Focus on breathing rhythm.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Two runs in the bank this week — that's real progress being built.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest before your long run tomorrow. A short walk is fine if you feel restless.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Long run of ~5 km at 7:30–8:00 /km — slightly easier than your midweek runs. The goal is time on feet, not speed. Walk breaks are completely fine if needed.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Sarah! This week is all about establishing your rhythm. Your three runs total 15 km — matching your current weekly volume so your body isn't shocked by anything new. The physiological goal right now is building your aerobic base: strengthening your heart, developing mitochondrial density in your muscles, and getting your connective tissue (tendons, ligaments) adapted to regular running stress. All three runs are at easy pace (7:00–8:00 /km), which keeps you in the aerobic zone where fat oxidation and cardiovascular adaptation happen most efficiently. There's no tempo or speed work yet — that comes later, once your foundation is solid. Think of this week as laying the first bricks. Consistency matters far more than intensity at this stage.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
